    "redesign_intro": {
      "type": "custom-liquid",
      "disabled": true,
      "name": "Redesign intro",
      "settings": {
        "custom_liquid": "<div class=\"page-width page-width--narrow\" style=\"padding:1rem 0 3rem; text-align:left;\">\n  <p style=\"font-size:1.6rem; line-height:1.7;\">Redesigning jewelry you already own is almost always more affordable than buying something new — because the most valuable parts, your stones and your gold, are already yours. Here's an honest look at what shapes the cost of a redesign, and how I price each piece.</p>\n  <h2>How much does jewelry redesign cost?</h2>\n  <p>Every redesign is one of a kind, so there's no flat price — it depends on the design, the materials, and the work involved. Because you supply your own gems and gold, you usually save a meaningful amount compared with buying a brand-new piece. After a free virtual consultation I give you a clear, itemized quote before any work begins, so there are never surprises.</p>\n  <h2>What affects the cost of a redesign?</h2>\n  <ul>\n    <li><strong>Design complexity</strong> — a simple resetting costs less than an intricate, fully custom piece.</li>\n    <li><strong>Metal</strong> — how much new gold or platinum is needed beyond what you supply, at current market prices.</li>\n    <li><strong>Stones</strong> — whether we reuse your own diamonds and gemstones (most affordable) or source new ones.</li>\n    <li><strong>Setting &amp; labor</strong> — the number of stones and the setting style.</li>\n    <li><strong>Finishing</strong> — engraving, textures, or special finishes.</li>\n  </ul>\n  <h2>Does using my own gold and stones make it cheaper?</h2>\n  <p>Yes. If you have gold or platinum you no longer wear, I responsibly refine it and apply its value toward your new piece. Reusing your own diamonds and gemstones means you aren't paying for new stones — often the single biggest cost in fine jewelry. You keep the sentiment, lower the cost, and it's kinder to the environment. <a href=\"/pages/use-your-own-gems-metal\">See how using your own gold works →</a></p>\n  <h2>How much does it cost to reset a diamond?</h2>\n  <p>Resetting is one of the most affordable redesigns, because your center stone — usually the most expensive part of a ring — is already yours. You're mainly paying for the new setting and the setting work. <a href=\"/pages/reset-diamond-ring\">Learn about diamond &amp; gemstone resetting →</a></p>\n  <h2>How much does it cost to redesign an engagement ring?</h2>\n  <p>When we reuse your existing diamond and gold, an engagement ring redesign costs far less than commissioning a new ring from scratch. The price reflects the new design and any additional metal or accent stones. <a href=\"/pages/redesign-engagement-ring\">See engagement ring redesign →</a></p>\n  <h2>How much does it cost to remake a wedding band?</h2>\n  <p>Remaking or redesigning a wedding band is one of the most budget-friendly projects, especially when I refine and reuse your original gold. The cost depends on the new design and the metal weight.</p>\n  <h2>How much does it cost to turn a ring into a necklace?</h2>\n  <p>Turning a ring into a pendant or necklace is a popular, sentimental redesign. The cost depends on the new setting and chain — and reusing your own stone and gold keeps it affordable. <a href=\"/pages/heirloom-jewelry-redesign\">Explore heirloom redesign →</a></p>\n  <h2>How do I get a price for my redesign?</h2>\n  <p>It's simple and free: book a complimentary virtual consultation, send me photos of your pieces, and I'll create a design and a transparent, itemized quote — before any work begins. Nothing proceeds until you approve it.</p>\n  <p style=\"margin-top:2.5rem;\"><a href=\"/pages/contact\" class=\"button\">Book your free consultation</a></p>\n</div>",
        "color_scheme": "",
        "padding_top": 24,
        "padding_bottom": 12
      }
    },
